SIMPLE: paw
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paw
<hw>Paw</hw> <pr>(p⟦add⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>pawe</ets>,
<ets>poue</ets>, OF. <ets>poe</ets>: cf. <ets>patte</ets>, LG.
<ets>pote</ets>, D. <ets>poot</ets>, G. <ets>pfote</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The foot of a quadruped having claws, as the lion, dog,
cat, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The hand.</def> <mark>[Jocose]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Paw clam</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the tridacna;
-- so called because shaped like an animal's
<xex>paw</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Paw
<hw>Paw</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To draw the forefoot along the
ground; to beat or scrape with the forefoot.</def> <rj><au>Job xxxix.
21.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Paw
<hw>Paw</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Pawed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pawing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To pass the paw over;
to stroke or handle with the paws; hence, to handle fondly or
rudely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To scrape or beat with the forefoot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His hot courser <qex>pawed</qex> the Hungarian plane.</q>
<rj><qau>Tickell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pawk</ent>⟦br⟧
